<LP>
   Good-Guy Blues
                                                                                                       

</LP>
<TEXT>
   After working on many a thankless task,
   With humdrum labor galore,
   I've found it's not the task that's thankless,
   But the folks I'm doing it for.
   -- Edward F. Dempsey.
   ---
   Repartee
                                                                                                       

   Backward, turn backward,
   O time in your flight;
   I just thought of a retort
   I needed last night.
   -- Gail Cooke.
   ---
   Profitable Perk
                                                                                                       

   One company provided etiquette seminars for its employees,
and used them as a tact write-off.
   -- Rodney Stevens.
